data.name: DataTypes
data.value:

data.name: EntityTypes
data.value:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-16"?><ArrayOfEntityType xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
<EntityType><EntityTypeCode>1</EntityTypeCode><EntityTypeName>Lookup</EntityTypeName><Description>For lookup entities.</Description></EntityType>
<EntityType><EntityTypeCode>2</EntityTypeCode><EntityTypeName>Lookup Business</EntityTypeName><Description>For key lookup entities that drive business rules.</Description></EntityType>
<EntityType><EntityTypeCode>3</EntityTypeCode><EntityTypeName>Primary</EntityTypeName><Description>For primary entities.</Description></EntityType>
<EntityType><EntityTypeCode>4</EntityTypeCode><EntityTypeName>Primary Coded</EntityTypeName><Description>For primary entities whose identifiers are manually determined.</Description></EntityType>
<EntityType><EntityTypeCode>5</EntityTypeCode><EntityTypeName>Primary Business</EntityTypeName><Description>For primary coded entities that drive business rules.</Description></EntityType>
<EntityType><EntityTypeCode>6</EntityTypeCode><EntityTypeName>Primary Logging</EntityTypeName><Description>For logging entities.</Description></EntityType>
<EntityType><EntityTypeCode>8</EntityTypeCode><EntityTypeName>Relational</EntityTypeName><Description>For entities that relate 2 or more other entities.</Description></EntityType>
</ArrayOfEntityType>

data.name: IdentifierTypes
data.value:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-16"?><ArrayOfIdentifierType xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
<IdentifierType><IdentifierTypeCode>1</IdentifierTypeCode><IdentifierTypeName>Generated</IdentifierTypeName><Description>For identifiers that are automatically generated.</Description></IdentifierType>
<IdentifierType><IdentifierTypeCode>2</IdentifierTypeCode><IdentifierTypeName>Coded</IdentifierTypeName><Description>For identifiers that are manually set (usually for business rules).</Description></IdentifierType>
<IdentifierType><IdentifierTypeCode>3</IdentifierTypeCode><IdentifierTypeName>Foreign Key</IdentifierTypeName><Description>For identifiers that are foreign keys.</Description></IdentifierType>
<IdentifierType><IdentifierTypeCode>4</IdentifierTypeCode><IdentifierTypeName>Multiple Column</IdentifierTypeName><Description>For identifiers that span multiple columns (and are not part of the same foreign key).</Description></IdentifierType>
</ArrayOfIdentifierType>
